{"WHIR":[{"def":"To whirl round, or revolve, with a whizzing noise; to fly or more quickly with a buzzing or whizzing sound; to whiz.","pos":""}],"WHIRL":[{"def":"To turn round rapidly; to cause to rotate with velocity; to make to revolve.","pos":""},{"def":"To remove or carry quickly with, or as with, a revolving motion; to snatch; to harry.","pos":""}],"WHIRL-BLAST":[{"def":"A whirling blast or wind.","pos":""}],"WHIRLABOUT":[{"def":"Something that whirls or turns about in a rapid manner; a whirligig.","pos":""}],"WHIRLBAT":[{"def":"Anything moved with a whirl, as preparatory for a blow, or to augment the force of it; -- applied by poets to the cestus of ancient boxers.","pos":""}],"WHIRLER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, whirls.","pos":""}],"WHIRLICOTE":[{"def":"An open car or chariot.","pos":""}],"WHIRLIGIG":[{"def":"Any one of numerous species of beetles belonging to Gyrinus and allied genera.","pos":""}],"WHIRLING":[{"def":"Whirl\"ing, Defn: a.","pos":""}],"WHIRLPOOL":[{"def":"A sea monster of the whale kind.","pos":""}],"WHIRLWIND":[{"def":"A violent windstorm of limited extent, as the tornado, characterized by an inward spiral motion of the air with an upward current in the center; a vortex of air.","pos":""}],"WHIRTLE":[{"def":"A perforated steel die through which wires or tubes are drawn to form them.","pos":""}]}